    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-20T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-20T06:00:00-05:00" n="46"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3965</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-20T13:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.40 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>926. Prime Minister and Minister for Foreign Affairs left Rome unexpectedly night
                    before last, incognito. Just learned they have gone France, believed for
                    conference touching Russia, where situation considered extremely grave, and for
                    greater Italian interests in eastern Mediterranean.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
